{"questionId":"4004","questionHtml":"<p>A black body emits radiation with its greatest intensity at a wavelength of I<sub>max</sub>. The surface&nbsp;temperature of the black body doubles without any other change occurring. What is the&nbsp;wavelength at which the greatest intensity of radiation is emitted?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;I<sub>max</sub></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{I}}{{\\text{}}_{{\\text{max}}}}}}{{\\text{2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>I</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>max</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>2</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{I}}{{\\text{}}_{{\\text{max}}}}}}{{\\text{4}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>I</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>max</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>4</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{I}}{{\\text{}}_{{\\text{max}}}}}}{{\\text{16}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>I</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>max</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>16</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markscheme